conservation_statuses.description: Although there are over 100 extant EOs for this species, most EOs appear to support only 1 or 2 pairs and it is not known whether these lower quality EOs are used on an annual basis. Population estimated to be between 555 and 2,360 breeding pairs. Many of the higher quality EOs have experienced declines and continue to receive pressure (direct and indirect) from development and recreational activities. Furthermore, this species is restricted to southern Ontario, mostly south of the Canadian Shield. Listed by COSEWIC as "vulnerable".

Special Concern: any species of wild animal native or once-native to North    Carolina which is determined by the Wildlife Resources Commission to    require monitoring but which may be taken under regulations adopted under    the provisions of this Article.

results.wikipedia_summary: The least bittern (Ixobrychus exilis) is a small heron, the smallest member of the family Ardeidae found in the Americas.
